</head><body><table width=90% align=center><tr><td class=textbody><center><h1>Quick Rundown on PoP Flagging</h1><br>by Gryphon</center><br><hr><b>Mithanial Marr Series</b><hr>
<b>Plane of Justice - Entry to Plane of Valor and the Plane of Storm</b>
<br>Find Mauvin in the heavily garded vault and talk him him. Then goto The Tribunal trials area and accept any trial, the Trial of Execution seems ot be the easiest. Once you kill the boss, look your Mark of [Trial] and head back to Mauvin. Hail him and recieve your flag.<br><br>
<b>Plane of Valor - Entry to the Halls of Honor</b><br>
Complete the quest to gain the key to Aerin`Dar's Keep. Slay Aerin`Dar and hail the Planar Projection, then fight you way down to the Halls of Honor zone in to complete the flag. You <u>must</u> zone into HoH from PoV once to complete your flag.<br><br>
<B>Halls of Honor - Entry to the Temple of Marr</b><br>
Complete the 3 trials found within the various three temples to gain entry to the Temple of Marr. The trials include: protecting a girl, protecting a village, slaying a dragon.<br><br>
<B>Temple of Marr - Part-Entry to the Tower of Solusek Ro</b><br>
Slay Mithanial Marr and hail the Planar Projection.
<br><br><br>
<hr><b>Agnarr Series</b><hr>
<b>Plane of Justice - Entry to Plane of Valor and the Plane of Storm</b>
<br>Find Mauvin in the heavily garded vault and talk him him. Then goto The Tribunal trials area and accept any trial, the Trial of Execution seems ot be the easiest. Once you kill the boss, look your Mark of [Trial] and head back to Mauvin. Hail him and recieve your flag.<br><br>
<B>Plane of Storms - Entry to Torden, the Basion of Thunder</b><BR>
Askr needs your help. He seeks a giant's beard, bone, sash and head. Hail him and do what he tells you to do. Then zone into Torden, the Bastion of Thunder via the tornado in the cave inhabited with frogs. You <u>must</u> zone into BoT from the tornado at least once to recieve your key.<br><br>
<B>Torden, the Bastion of Thunder - Part-Entry to the Tower of Solusek Ro</b><br>
Askr needs your help again. Get him 1 of each gem from the lower level of BoT, then get him 1 of each sphere from the Towers of BoT. Then go slay Agnarr the Storm Lord to free Karana. Talk with Karana to recieve your flag<br><br><br>
<hr><b>Terris Thule Series</b><hr>
<b>Plane of Nightmares - Entry to the Lair of Terris Thule</b><br>
Get the pre-flag from the sick house in PoT. Then head over to the Plane of Nightmares. Cross the chasm and find the hedge. Accept his quest and follow him around protecting him from danger. Once you kill the boss, hail the projection to complete the flag.<br><br>
<b>Lair of Terris Thule - Entry to Torment, Plane of Pain</b><br>
Traverse the ridge untill you see Terris Thule's abode. Kill her and hail the projection to complete the flag.<br><br><br>
<hr><b>Bertoxxulous Series</b><hr>
<B>Plane of Decay - Entry to the Crypt of Decay</b><br>
Get the pre-flag from the person standing next to the zone in. Slay Grummus and hail the Planar Projection. Then drop down the hole into the Crypt of Decay to finish the flag. You <u>must</u> drop down into CoD from PoD at least once to complete the flag.<br><br>
<b>Crypt of Decay - Entry to the Depths of the Crypt of Decay</b><br>
Slay Carpin to trigger a ring like event. Keep moving forward and slaying the various mini-bosses in your way. Then slay the High Priest himself and hail the rat to complete the flag. <u>Only 32 keys can be achieved per Carpin cycle.</u><br><br>
<B>Depths of the Crypt of Decay - Entry to Torment, Plane of Pain; Part-Entry to the Tower of Solusek Ro</b><br>
Kill the only mob down here to start the Bertoxxulous event. My only advice: kill fast. Slay Bertoxxulous and hail the projection to recieve the flag.<BR><BR><BR>
<HR><B>Rallos Zek Series</b><hr>
<b>Plane of Innovation Junkyard - Entry to the Plane of Innovation Factory</b><Br>
Trigger the quest with the gnome and follow him around protecting him. Eventually, he'll lead you to the dragon. Slay him to recieve the key to the Factory. You do not need the key to progress, but you need at least 1 person with it to open the factory door.<br><br>
<b>Plane of Innovation Factory - Entry to Drunder, the Fortress of Zek</b><br>
Slay the Manaetic Behemoth and hail Giwin to recieve the flag.<br><br>
<b>Drunder, Fortress of Zek - Part-Entry to the Tower of Solusek Ro</b><br>
Slay the Zek brothers, Tallon and Vallon. Hail the projection of recieve the flag.<br><Br>
<B>Drunder, Fortress of Zek - Entry to Eryslai, the Kingdom of Wind; the Reef of Coirnav; Vegarlson, the Earthen Badland; Part-Entry to Solusek Ro's Chamber</b><br>
Slay Rallos Zek the Warlord. Hail the projection to recieve your flag. Congratulations, you are now part elemental flaged!<br><br><br>
<hr><b>Solusek Ro Series</b><hr>
<B>Tower of Solusek Ro - Part-Entry to Solusek Ro's Chamber</b><br>
Slay the 5 minibosses: Jiva, Arylixir, Xuzl, Rizlona and the Protector of Dresolik to recieve party entry into Solusek Ro's chamber. Combined with Rallos Zek's flag, you can now port up into his chamber.<br><br>
<B>Tower of Solusek Ro, Solusek Ro's Chamber - Entry to Doomfire, the Burning Lands</b><br>
Slay Solusek Ro. Hail the projection and drop down the well into Doomfire. You <u>must</u> drop down into the well to finish off your flag.<br><br><br>
You are now fully elemental flagged. Enjoy your xp and loot!</td></tr></table></body></html>